	Problem Statement
Women in their 30s, 40s, and 50s face challenges re-entering the tech workforce after
career breaks. Underrepresentation, societal stereotypes, and rapid technological
changes create barriers that leave many feeling disconnected and unsure of how to
regain confidence in the evolving industry.
Our Vision: Tech Her Forward
Tech Her Forward is a podcast designed to empower middle-aged women to reimagine
their futures in tech. Through actionable insights, inspiring stories, and expert guidance,
we challenge biases, celebrate life experiences, and create pathways for women to
reclaim their place in the industry.
Podcast Overview
The podcast combines storytelling with practical resources to support women
navigating career transitions. Each episode explores unique challenges and provides
tools to rebuild skills and confidence in a safe and empowering space.
Why Tech Her Forward?
The name symbolizes resilience and progress—helping women move forward in their
careers. It serves as a bridge, connecting where women are now to where they aspire to
be, in a supportive environment for growth and learning.
Podcast Features
• Engaging Stories: Interviews with tech leaders, returnship advocates, and
women who successfully re-entered tech.
• Practical Resources: Guidance on upskilling, networking, and leveraging
returnship programs and mentorships.
• Leadership Focus: Building confidence, staying adaptable, and embracing
trends.
• Inclusion: Highlighting diverse voices and celebrating unique perspectives in
tech.
Audio Clips
We created four audio clips to showcase our podcast, accessible via QR codes at the
exhibition. Using cutting-edge tools like diffusion models, language models, and text-
to-speech technology, we crafted the podcast content, logo, and branding visuals.
Display Highlights
• Visual branding elements of Tech Her Forward.
• QR codes to listen to the audio clips and explore the podcast.
Impact
Tech Her Forward is more than a podcast—it’s a movement. By amplifying diverse
voices and leveraging innovation, we empower women to reclaim their place in tech.
Together, let’s build a more inclusive and resilient industry.
